@matt4.0 Hi Matt,
We have been selling Straton powered RTU's and IOT edge devices in India.
Brodersen RTU's (Denmark based) uses Straton as their configuration software.

> Question of the day: What is your preferred SCADA platform (one word answer)?  What is the real world difference, in your eyes, between SCADA and HMI?
@Walker Reynolds Siemens Simatic WINCC.
 SCADA system is comprised of remote systems all tied together at one central hub. SCADA systems are a combination of many systems including sensors, RTUs or Remote Terminal Units, and PLCs. HMI can be part of SCADA but SCADA cannot be part of a HMI. It’s that simple.

> Likewise on proprietary single board computers with non volatile memory relying on a coin battery for memory persistence.
@EgoNoBueno 
Thank you for these tips. Especially in the chemical industry the equipment are changed without being reused at the maintenance shutdown.

> Likewise on proprietary single board computers with non volatile memory relying on a coin battery for memory persistence.
@EgoNoBueno
Even some old laptop and PC would not start if the battery is depleted.

> @Na2$ Exactly, Cooling fans checks and battery checks are easy PM items that will save you a lot of grief. Analytical equipment that has sat in a cabinet, should receive the same periodic love. Batteries are cheap - a lot of equipment frustration is avoidable by these simple efforts.
@EgoNoBueno  The basics are always needed especially when you have a lot of equipment. The pity is, in the fertilizer chemistry industry, you can not open the sensors, and change the internal condensator or batteries to avoid a chemical hazard. Only companies selling the sensors are authorized to open them and the certification is costly. This implies high maintenance costs.
